ce:section.ce:para:
FeCu–P/CDs are a class of nanomaterials with a variety of enzyme-like activities, which can simulate the function of natural enzymes (Scheme 1
                        ). FeCu–P/CDs nanozymes exhibit POD-like, HPO-like and SOD-like catalytic activities. The simulation of POD-like and HPO-like enzyme activities can catalyze the production of highly toxic ·OH and HBrO/HClO, thereby providing a dual pathway for the elimination of bacteria. Specifically, FeCu–P/CDs nanozymes show excellent POD-like catalytic activity with a specific activity of 37.9 U/mg, which can catalyze the decomposition of H2O2 to generate highly toxic ·OH for elimination of bacteria. The experimental results show the antibacterial rate of FeCu–P/CDs nanozymes against E. Coli at 25 μg/mL was more than 99.9 % in an acidic environment. In addition, FeCu–P/CDs nanozymes can catalyze the reaction of H2O2 and Br− to generate HBrO through HPO-like catalytic activity, which is used for elimination of bacteria in a neutral environment. Furthermore, FeCu–P/CDs nanozymes can simulate the activity of SOD-like enzyme, and transform •O2
                        − into more toxic ·OH through the SOD-POD cascade catalytic reaction.
